Put a large #saucepan{} of water with a @salt{pinch} on to boil for the noodles. Peel
and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve, then remove the cores
from the @Bell Pepper{1} and @Yellow Pepper{½} and chop into bite-sized chunks. Remove
the root from the @spring onion{1}(separated into white and green parts) and thinly slice,
separating the white and green parts. Add the @egg noodle nest{2} to the boiling water
and simmer until cooked, ~{4%minutes}. Then drain in a #colander{} and immediately
submerge in cold water.

Cut the @British pork loin steaks{2} into roughly 2cm cubes. Remember to wash your hands
afterwards! Put the @cornflour{10} in a #mixing bowl{} and season with a generous
pinch of @salt{generous pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{good grind}. Add the
pork and toss to coat thoroughly.

Put a #frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil). Add the @sesame seeds{7.5} and toast until
golden, ~{1-2%minutes}. Toss and stir them regularly so they don't burn. Remove from
the pan and set aside. Wipe out your pan with some #kitchen paper{}.

Put the frying pan back on high heat and add a splash of @?oil{}. Line a #plate{} with
kitchen paper. When the oil is hot, add half the pork. Stir-fry until browned on the
outside and no longer pink in the middle, ~{6-7%minutes}. Transfer to the lined plate.
Add a little more oil to the pan and fry the remaining pork in the same way.

> Cooking in batches = extra crispy!

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, mix the @rice vinegar{15} and @soy sauce{12.5} with the
@ketjap manis{37.5} and @tomato ketchup{1}. This is your sauce. Wash the frying pan
you used for the pork, add another splash of oil and put it on medium heat. Stir-fry
the peppers for ~{4%minutes}. Add the garlic and the whites of the spring onion.
Cook for another ~{1%minute}. Add the sauce and bring to a simmer.

Return the pork to the pan. Drain the noodles again, add them to the pan too and toss
everything together. Lower the heat to medium and heat everything through. Taste and
season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} if needed. Serve in #bowls{}. Sprinkle the
greens of the spring onion and sesame seeds onto the adults' portions. Enjoy!